Exactly what is the point to wakening up an unkillable creature? Pride? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
In a way, yes. <br>
<br>
Everyone plays for different reasons. There exists a large contingent of people who play Everquest to be the &quot;first&quot; to do something on a server. The first person to level 50, and then 60. The first person to have X weapon, or a full suit of Y armor. The first guild to kill Vindicator, AoW, Emperor... etc. <br>
<br>
These encounters create a type of lore, or history, for a given guild, and a given server. On many servers people can still remember who was the first person to get the first surname, or who was the first monk to 50 was (back when 60 wasn't even possible). They remember the first guild that cleared the Plane of Fear, or the first guild to kill Tunare. <br>
<br>
<br>
The Sleeper adds to this lore because not only is it a first, but a LAST as well. The guild that does it can lay claim to being the first guild to do it, and the only guild to do it, for that server. <br>
<br>
<br>
It's odd.. I read complaints on boards like this all the time, about how there is no lore in Everquest, and there is no storyline. And yet whenever a big guild does something for the first time, or something worth remembering, everyone dismisses it as &quot;oh, that's just the uberguilds being d00dz and trying to get phat l3wtz&quot;. <br>
<br>
<br>
In the guild I'm in on Rodcet Nife (yes, I've returned there and split some time with FV now), the &quot;old timers&quot; in my guild can recall events from over two years ago. Our first trip to Fear, or first guild raid into Lower Guk, or our first time into NToV. <br>
<br>
We don't remember who got what loot, because it's irrelivent. But we remember the adventure... <br>
<br>
Those of you who aren't wired with this kind of mindset will probably never understand the motivation behind this type of thing. I can't make you understand. All I can do is tell you how some people view certain things. <br>
<br>
For a lot of people, being first, or being best, is important to them. Even if it's being first or best in a &quot;game&quot;. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
-Krazak<br>
